Where could they have gone?

272
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:20,460
They didn't go deeper into the maze,
did they?

273
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:21,780
That'd be my guess!

274
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:26,000
These deciphered hieroglyphs tell me the
inside of these ruins is a giant labyrinth.

275
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:29,760
So if that is the case... They
could be lost in there forever!

276
00:10:30,820 --> 00:10:31,820
Forever?!

277
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:37,900
Hey, uh, Tentamon?

278
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:38,360
Yes?

279
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:41,180
You get the feeling we're sort of going
around in circles?

280
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,800
See this sooty smudge on the wall?

281
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,100
I remember passing it a long time ago!

282
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:46,860
You're right!

283
00:10:47,220 --> 00:10:48,540
Could it be that we're lost?

284
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:54,061
I realize this is probably a bad time
to say I told you so, but... Oh, quiet!

285
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:57,000
Oh, I can't bear it!

286
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:57,660
I'm going in!

287
00:10:57,780 --> 00:10:58,680
And get lost too?

288
00:10:58,681 --> 00:10:59,681
No, Palmon!

289
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,400
We have got to use our heads first!

290
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,200
But we can't just leave them!

291
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,200
We won't!

292
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:06,540
But this is one super complicated maze!

293
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:08,820
I've got to try to get a handle on it!

294
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:11,180
Then maybe I can help get them out!

295
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:14,300
Well, being lost isn't so bad!

296
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:15,420
Great!

297
00:11:15,421 --> 00:11:16,421
Oh dear!

298
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:17,540
Are you hurt?

299
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,140
No, I'm fine!

300
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:20,660
I'm getting used to it by now!

301
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:23,916
If I'd just gotten to cheerleading camp,
none of this would have happened!

302
00:11:23,940 --> 00:11:25,980
Let's try a systematic approach to this.

303
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:29,920
Maybe if we just keep turning to the left
or something like that...

304
00:11:29,921 --> 00:11:31,060
Why should I listen to you?

305
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:34,000
It's your friend Izzy that got me into
this mess in the first place!

306
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:34,380
Wait!

307
00:11:34,580 --> 00:11:35,580
Don't be too hard on him!

308
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:37,947
Yes, he gets a little wrapped
up in his work and doesn't

309
00:11:37,948 --> 00:11:40,680
always interact well with
others, but he's a good boy!

310
00:11:41,860 --> 00:11:42,880
There they are!

311
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,380
That's Mimi, that blinking light?

312
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:48,980
Precisely!

313
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:54,920
Oh, that's my girl!

314
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,460
I've honed in on the signal from her
digivice!

315
00:11:57,820 --> 00:11:58,840
We can hear her!

316
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:00,260
Let's hope she can hear us!

317
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,760
Izzy to Mimi, do you read me?

318
00:12:04,060 --> 00:12:05,460
Repeat, do you read me?

319
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,600
Izzy, is that you?

320
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:08,180
Oh right, it's working!

321
00:12:08,540 --> 00:12:12,300
Okay, Mimi, I'm gonna navigate for you,
so walk exactly where I tell you to!

322
00:12:13,220 --> 00:12:14,680
Don't worry, it'll be okay!

323
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,240
He knows what he's doing!

324
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,600
Is that you, Palmon?

325
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:21,080
Just do what Izzy tells you and you'll be
out of there before you know it!

326
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:23,060
See, I told you Izzy was a good boy!

327
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,900
Okay, now take the first doorway on the
right.

328
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,960
When you get to the end, turn left.

329
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,364
But be careful of the
next room because

330
00:12:29,365 --> 00:12:32,241
there's a big hole in
the middle of the floor.

331
00:12:37,470 --> 00:12:40,030
There should be a narrow ledge you can use
to get across!

332
00:12:40,031 --> 00:12:43,910
Uh, Izzy, did we have to take the scenic
route?

333
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:51,290
Uh-oh, what do you mean uh-oh?

334
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:54,190
Okay, I'm ready, which way should we go?

335
00:12:55,070 --> 00:12:56,410
Something has happened.

336
00:12:56,990 --> 00:12:59,170
I was hoping it was just a glitch.

337
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:03,650
But there's definitely something in that
maze with them and it's moving closer.

338
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:05,590
Now I am starting to worry.

339
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:07,770
Izzy, what's with the silent treatment?

340
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:10,050
Did you hear that?

341
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:11,810
It sounded evil.

342
00:13:12,710 --> 00:13:15,030
Tantamon, it's been such a long time.

343
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:16,270
Oh no!

344
00:13:18,530 --> 00:13:19,850
St. Taramon!

345
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,510
Half man, half horse!

346
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:24,310
You really don't want to get on either of
his bad sides!

347
00:13:26,710 --> 00:13:27,890
Come on, Nini, run!

348
00:13:28,050 --> 00:13:29,330
I like a good chase.

349
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:30,570
Take a wrap!

350
00:13:34,210 --> 00:13:37,130
Izzy, we are quite anxiously awaiting your
directions.

351
00:13:37,131 --> 00:13:38,410
Are you there?

352
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:39,870
Another lap!

353
00:13:39,970 --> 00:13:40,630
Through the doorway!

354
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:41,830
This way, Nini!

355
00:13:43,330 --> 00:13:44,510
Great job, Izzy!

356
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:45,270
It's a dead end!

357
00:13:45,350 --> 00:13:46,670
Where do we go now, Izzy?

358
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:48,490
Izzy, hello!

359
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:51,410
We seem to have lost contact with him.

360
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:52,170
Oh, really?

361
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:53,430
He's back!

362
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:54,950
Solar Ray!

363
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:57,310
Fire!

364
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:09,840
Your bravery is noted, but that alone will
not gain you any mercy.

365
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,260
What are you waiting for?

366
00:14:11,340 --> 00:14:12,080
Make yourself bigger!

367
00:14:12,081 --> 00:14:15,340
If you mean you want me to digivolve,
I'm afraid that's impossible.

368
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,040
What do you mean, impossible?

369
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,700
I'll tell you what he means.

370
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:23,020
He cannot protect you, so you have to hold
your ground, and that's truly impossible.

371
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:24,200
Stop talking!

372
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:24,780
Get going!

373
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:28,060
Oh, how I'd like to, but if I'm separated
from Izzy, I can!

374
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:28,500
Ah!

375
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,580
Stop that!

376
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,760
Can't you see I'm in the middle of saying
something?

377
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:33,900
What's that practice?

378
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:39,360
Izzy!

379
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:40,820
Get out of there!

380
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:41,260
Hurry!

381
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:41,820
Come on!

382
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,220
You don't have to tell me twice!

383
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:44,940
Watch out, Izzy!

384
00:14:44,941 --> 00:14:47,700
I don't want this, Izzy!

385
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:52,040
I'm ready if I'm

386
00:14:57,150 --> 00:15:02,210
ready for a break.

387
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:06,470
I won't take your hand for this.후!

388
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:26,600
Oh... And come
on, Digivolve to...

389
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:29,460
Kabu Terrimon!

390
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,480
Oh!

391
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:36,440
I forgot, when you get bigger,
you get a lot bigger, don't you?

392
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:37,840
Watch for your step!

393
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,160
Oh, uh, sorry.

394
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:53,080
Yeah, but this is no time for us to start
taking it easy.

395
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:54,560
Look who's here!

396
00:15:54,860 --> 00:15:56,540
Yeah, I see him!

397
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:57,800
Leave them alone!

398
00:15:59,620 --> 00:16:00,660
Electro Shocker!

399
00:16:00,661 --> 00:16:03,540
I think it's time for a needle spray!

400
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,660
That felt interesting.

401
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:17,800
One of those black ears fell out of his
body.

402
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,480
Where am I?

403
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,000
Are you a good Digimon now?

404
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:26,740
Hm?

405
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:27,260
What?

406
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:29,060
That device on your bag.

407
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:31,660
This?

408
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,420
I have seen it before.

409
00:16:34,940 --> 00:16:37,780
It is the mystical symbol of the Digivice.

410
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,640
These ruins are its temple.

411
00:16:39,860 --> 00:16:41,100
And I am its guardian.

412
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,400
Well, that certainly looks familiar.

413
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:46,920
The Digivice is a preserver of the light.

414
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:50,800
A last line of defense against the
darkness that threatens existence.

415
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,040
Really?

416
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,740
I didn't get that.

417
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,560
But I'm starting to think they're more
than just a cool accessory.

418
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:58,620
Liomon!

419
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Why are you here?

420
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,660
To destroy them.

421
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:04,920
The children.

422
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:05,980
What?

423
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:07,680
I warn you, Sentaruman.

424
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,280
Do not interfere with me.

425
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,360
No, Liomon!

426
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,520
I can't look.

427
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:18,660
It's too scary.

428
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:19,700
Well, maybe a peep.

429
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,080
Whoa.

430
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,920
Time's standing still here.

431
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:25,020
I said no, Liomon.

432
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,540
The children possess the Digivice.

433
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:31,060
As the guardian of its temple,
I must protect them as well.

434
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,920
Protect them from me?

435
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,160
Good luck.

436
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:37,720
Fist of the Beast King!

437
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,600
Solar Ray!

438
00:17:41,780 --> 00:17:45,580
Now let's stop this madness before one of
us is hurt.

439
00:17:46,060 --> 00:17:47,060
Liomon?

440
00:17:56,620 --> 00:17:59,060
The children must be... destroyed!

441
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,760
Your Digivice!

442
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,620
It stopped him in his tracks!

443
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:12,660
Bad Kitty!

444
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:13,120
Out!

445
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:13,920
Go on!

446
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,100
Out!

447
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,300
Well, that got rid of him.

448
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,540
These things really are kind of amazing.

449
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,300
A preserver of light against the darkness.

450
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:37,940
Can you order a pizza with it?

451
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,000
I'm still starving.

452
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:44,520
Sentaruman, maybe with your help,
we could stop this black ear.

453
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:47,836
No, I'm afraid I have
neither the strength nor the

454
00:18:47,837 --> 00:18:50,800
knowledge to oppose Devimon
and the powers of darkness.

455
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,220
Are you still going on about that?

456
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:55,260
When could we start looking for something
to eat?

457
00:18:55,700 --> 00:19:00,121
Guess I'll just have to keep deciphering
and analyzing these two sets of pyroglyphs.

458
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,580
I'm sure all the answers are in here
somewhere.

459
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,300
Excuse me, isn't this where I came in?

460
00:19:05,340 --> 00:19:07,240
You're not seriously starting all that
again?

461
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,440
Not right now!

462
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,480
Just a nano.

463
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,380
This black gear!

464
00:19:11,540 --> 00:19:13,160
Who cares about that dumb old thing?

465
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:14,300
All I want is lunch!

466
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:19,300
Look,

467
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,100
the process has reversed itself.

468
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,640
Amazing!

469
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:28,900
Excellent work, Mimi.

470
00:19:29,060 --> 00:19:32,820
It just goes to show you that sometimes
the simplest solution is actually the best.

471
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,280
That's not much of a compliment.

472
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:35,480
Well, are you?

473
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:37,260
I knew you couldn't keep away.

474
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:38,740
Huh?

475
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,680
So are we gonna go on a date or what?

476
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:43,640
Come on, what's your phone number?

477
00:19:43,980 --> 00:19:45,360
Man, he is persistent.

478
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:47,220
At least blow us a kiss!

479
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,440
Okay!

480
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:51,040
Oh, come on!

481
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,320
Do it like you mean it!

482
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:54,340
You know you like us, you know you do,
please!

483
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:18,900
I love you!

